benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails - Retrieve an account emails

covered: Valid request and response format (TC01, TC14): 200 OK, Content-Type application/json, JSON array of AccountEmail objects and expected fields present
Empty response handling (TC02, TC04): accounts with no emails and non-existent valid UUIDs return empty arrays
Path parameter validation (TC03): invalid accountId format returns 400 with an error message
Authentication and authorization (TC05): missing or invalid token results in 401/403
Service unavailability (TC06): 503 handling for server down/unreachable
Query parameter handling (TC07): unknown/extra query parameters are ignored
Large dataset and performance (TC08): behavior with 1000+ emails and response time constraint
Concurrency and stress (TC13): concurrent requests behavior and response-time checks
Security tests (TC10, TC11): SQL injection and XSS attempts produce safe error responses and do not leak internals
Special characters and unicode (TC12): emails with special/unicode characters are returned correctly
Transient failure and retry behavior (TC09): client retry/timeout scenarios considered
Accessibility and backward compatibility (TC14, TC15): compatibility of JSON structure and accessible error messages
gaps: Pagination: No tests for pagination semantics (limit/offset/page, ordering, total counts or page boundaries) for large result sets
Comprehensive query parameter validation: only an extra ignored param is tested; no tests for allowed query params, invalid types, or combinations
Full schema validation: tests check a few fields but do not validate the full AccountEmail JSON schema (types, required fields, nested properties)
Rate limiting and throttling: no tests simulate bursts to verify 429 responses, Retry-After headers or throttling behavior
Caching and conditional requests: no tests for ETag, If-None-Match, Cache-Control headers or 304 Not Modified behavior
Server side error coverage: 500 Internal Server Error and graceful handling of unexpected server failures are not exercised
Header and content negotiation checks: beyond Content-Type there are no checks for Accept header handling, ETag, Content-Length, etc.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: exercise limit/offset or page parameters, boundary values, sorting and verify stable ordering and any metadata (totalCount, page size)
Add full JSON schema validation against definitions/AccountEmail for all success responses to ensure types, required fields and contract stability
Add rate limiting tests: simulate request bursts to validate 429 behavior, Retry-After header and that legitimate clients are not unfairly throttled
Add caching tests: verify ETag and Cache-Control headers, conditional GET with If-None-Match returns 304 where appropriate and headers are present and correct
Add server error simulations: force/spy 500 internal errors (e.g., DB failure) to validate safe error responses and no leakage of stack traces or internals
Expand query parameter tests: validate handling of unknown, malformed or multiple query params and behavior when query param names collide with reserved names
Extend security tests: add OWASP style tests such as long input, header injection and path traversal; verify length limits and input sanitization
Add header and content negotiation tests: vary Accept and Accept-Encoding headers and assert correct Content-Type and encoding behavior
Make performance and concurrency tests reproducible: define SLAs, use controlled load tools in CI, and include assertions on percentiles (p95, p99) rather than single response time checks
Introduce contract tests and deterministic test data setup/teardown so scenarios are repeatable and protect against regressions
